Citation.sAbstract: The temperature dependence of the total vapor pressure of GaBr3 measured by the torsion-effusion method  over the temperature range (300 to 357) K is represented by the following equation: log(p/Pa) ) (16.1 (  0.6) - (5250 ( 200)(K/T). This compound sublimes to the monomer and dimer species. From the temperature  dependence of the dissociation, and the equilibrium constant of the dimer found in the literature, the partial  pressures of both forms were evaluated from which the second- and third-law standard enthalpies of the  sublimation reactions, GaBr3(s) ) GaBr3(g) and GaBr3(s) ) 1/2Ga2Br6(g), were calculated: AsubHdeg (298 K)  ) (92.5 ( 2.0) kJ * mol-1 and (50.5 ( 2.0) kJ * mol-1 for the monomer and dimer forms, respectively.
Citation.sTitle: A Study on the Sublimation of Gallium Tribromide
